Boko Haram militants abducted 276 Nigerian schoolgirls last year . 
  More than 200 of the girls remain in captivity and scores of other children have gone missing . 
  Unicef has launched a campaign to raise awareness of the situation in Nigeria . 
  Many children have been forced from their homes by the conflict . 
  Some have been used by the militants as sex slaves and fighters . 
  Many have fled to refugee camps where they are being educated . 
 